Toro Rosso technical chief James Key:<br />
<br />
&ldquo;<span style="color: red;">We have run three engines</span> but only because we were cycling them in the first test - we didn't have to do that, and we've run one in the second test. That's just a plan, not because we had to. It's been super reliable so far so fingers crossed that continues. It's the best PU reliability we've had since the PU era began, so very happy.&quot;

